snippet.title: Thank You - Jason Kelce Officially Retires
snippet.description:
After 13 season as the Philadelphia Eagles' starting center, Jason Kelce is officially retiring from the NFL. One of the greatest of all time, Kelce finishes his career as a seven-time Pro Bowler, six-time First-Team All-Pro, and most importantly, a Super Bowl Champion, helping bring the City of Brotherly Love its first Super Bowl victory during the historic 2017 season.

Jason Kelce has shown the football world what it means to be an Eagle throughout the entirety of his years in Midnight Green. Congratulations on an incredible run, Jason. Thank you!

snippet.title: NASA's SpaceX Crew-8 Launch (Official NASA Broadcast)
snippet.description:
Watch live with us as a crew of four launch on NASA's SpaceX Crew-8 mission to the International Space Station. Liftoff is targeted at 10:53 p.m. EST (0353 UTC), Sunday, March 3.

The launch attempt March 2 was postponed due to unfavorable conditions in the flight path of the SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket and Dragon spacecraft.
 
The crew will lift off in their SpaceX Dragon spacecraft, powered by a Falcon 9 rocket, from Launch Complex 39A at NASA's Kennedy Space Center in Florida. Members include:
• NASA astronaut Matthew Dominick, commander
• NASA astronaut Michael Barratt, pilot
• NASA astronaut Jeanette Epps, mission specialist
• Roscosmos cosmonaut Aleksandr Grebenkin, mission specialist
 
Visit our Crew-8 blog for the latest mission news: https://blogs.nasa.gov/crew-8 
 
Over 200 science experiments and technology demonstrations will take place during Crew-8's mission of approximately six months in space. Experiments will include using stem cells to create organoid models to study degenerative diseases, studying the effects of microgravity and UV radiation on plants at a cellular level, and testing whether wearing pressure cuffs on the legs could prevent fluid shifts and reduce health problems in astronauts. Learn more about the mission and science at: https://www.nasa.gov/missions/station/commercial-crew/what-you-need-to-know-about-nasas-spacex-crew-8-mission/
 
Thumbnail credit: SpaceX

Credit: NASA
 
#NASA #Crew8

snippet.title: I Watched Every Barbie Movie Ever Made
snippet.description:
Let our Sponsor BetterHelp connect you to a therapist who can support you - all from the comfort of your own home. Visit https://BetterHelp.com/TedNivison and enjoy a special discount on your first month.

In this video I embarked on the greatest challenge yet: Watching every Barbie movie ever made and constructed a theory that discovers the true lore of Barbie, all while maintaining my sanity. Enjoy!

FOLLOW ME
► https://www.instagram.com/tednivison
► https://twitter.com/TedNivison

► OTHER STUFF: https://linktr.ee/tednivison

Assistant Editor: https://www.instagram.com/ReallyZade

Have an idea you want covered? Submit here: https://forms.gle/wzbXDHqEZZJHwz958

Custom Music by Oval:  @OvalMusic  
Outro: Pls Proceed by Baron Grand
Royalty Free Music by 
http://www.epidemicsound.com/

FMC (Frequently Made Comments): 

"Ted doesn't know about modern monarchies like the U.K."

I'm aware of the fact that there are monarchies in the world today. What I was trying to figure out was if Mirabella was an "absolute monarchy," as in the monarch is the sole legislative power in the nation. In the case of something like the United Kingdom, that is a constitutional monarchy where the monarch has very little, to almost zero power in the actual workings of the government. There are 7 countries in the world today with absolute monarchies, and one of them funnily enough is The Vatican. 

"I cannot believe that he rated _____ so low" 

I would not take my actual numbered ratings too seriously, as they can seriously be crippled by both the moral and sidekick ratings - which, honestly, are totally ridiculous categories to judge the movies and half the time I gave a zero if they didn't have them. If you are a Barbie fanatic, and genuinely liked a movie that I rated low, I'd suggest taking my "Barbie" and "Story" ratings, and then make that number out of 10. That's probably a more "real" rating for the Barbie movie.

snippet.title: World’s First Cybertruck On TRACKS Is Crazier Than You Think!
snippet.description:
Go to https://drinkag1.com/heavydsparks to get a free year supply of vitamin d3k
2, and 10 extra travel packs of AG1! 

Can't thank ​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠@supercar_ron enough for making this happen! If you're not following Ron please stop what your doing and give him a follow! This wild project wouldn't have happened without him donating his NEW Cyber truck! This dude has has a handful of VERY VERY Viral videos and is one hell of an entertainer, so please show him some love! 
​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠@supercar_ron ​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠@supercar_ron ​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠​⁠@supercar_ron 

Huge shout out to Baja Designs for sending out the lights! The second the first picture of this thing was posted they immediately reached out to help! The lights that we picked out for this project are the new LP9 Lights. The guys in the shop were able to make this clean light rack for the top of the truck that flows so well with the lines of the truck. We have the lights tied into their own battery bank that we have mounted in the bed of the truck so it doesn't pull any energy from the truck. We love they way they turned out on this truck! If you're in the market for the brightest lights in the game please go check them out!
https://www.bajadesigns.com/

We also want to give a huge shout out to ArcticFX! I had a vision in my mind on what I wanted but couldn't get it dialed in just right till I handed the design work over to their team. Once design was dialed in they sent the wrap out and made it happen! We've been using ArcticFX for years now helping us with everything from my personal sleds to our giveaway trucks, they are absolute animals in the wrap game. If you are in the market for a new wrap for your sled/UTV/Bike please hit them up. They truly have changed the custom wrap game!

You can win one of my personal vehicles by subscribing to all of my channels right now!
